&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Surgical SDEC &amp; SAU Physician Associate - Emergency Surgery, Band 7&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed term/Secondment: 12 months due to funding&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to be involved in the set-up of Surgical Same Day Emergency Care pathways. The post holders will contribute to day to day management of referrals and delivery of surgical input into Ambulatory Care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The roles will be based at either Chelsea and Westminster Hospital or West Middlesex University Hospital within Ambulatory Care and Emergency department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post would suit a PA who wants to increase and develop their clinical experience of emergency general surgery. This post will be focused in Ambulatory care and the Emergency department, operating as a key link in Surgical Same Day Emergency Pathways (SSDEC). There will be an opportunity to gain knowledge across other emergency surgery specialties, including Plastics and Trauma and Orthopaedics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Participation in service co-ordination and quality improvement will be integral to this role, particularly as we aim to transfer a bulk of surgical activity to SSDEC pathways this winter to free-up bed capacity. The post-holder will work alongside surgeons and the SSDEC lead nurse to ensure SSDEC pathways operate at full functionality. The post holder will also have an integral role in developing and implementing new surgical ambulatory pathways.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Will Reynolds, Divisional Head of Service Improvement - Planned Care&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;email: will.reynolds@chelwest.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel. 07796146214&lt;/p&gt;
